==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ultragaseous
<hw>Ul`tra*gas"e*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>ultra</ets> + <ets>gaseous</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld>
<def>Having the properties exhibited by gases under very low pressures
(one millionth of an atmosphere or less). Matter under this condition,
which has been termed <xex>the fourth state of matter</xex>, is
sometimes called <xex>radiant matter</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ultrage</ent>⟦br⟧
